item.description:
Presenter: Matt Martel

This will be an overview on how to get started in iPhone development. Topics include: equipment needed; registering as an iphone developer; setting up a development team; installing sdk and tools; your first iphone application; submitting to the App Store; and more.

Even though this will be pretty high-level (I'm not going to teach you Objective-C or Cocoa frameworks) it should be of general interest to folks that are already developing for the iPhone OS. I'll share some of the things I've learned the hard way in the last year and a half.
item.how_to_find_us: Large meeting room on lower level
item.name: Beginning iPhone Development
